      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KEELEY ROSE (4) turned heads when posting a superb 30.78 over 531m at Gawler three back then has hit the frame in both runs since. Hot win three back and looks the one to beat here. JALAPENO GEM (2) had a tough draw to overcome and was game in defeat when only a neck from Black Chip in second (31.40) at this track. Smart beginner who should take advantage of the low draw. Will give a great sight again. RANDOM SASS (8) ran a good time (37.91) when placing three back at Gawler but has missed the frame since, last time out finishing fifth (31.18) at this track. Solid beginner and with a good start should have clear running out wide. Can improve sharply here. KISSES FOR AMY (6) looks a top-three hope after a break.",
